			<ns0:name>bradc...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/110304265766688778552/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Today garbage collectors cannot be implemented in NaCl because it is not possible to stop all threads.

We need a solution that allows garbage collection. The most obvious approach involves stopping all threads, then allowing a designated GC thread to do its work. Is there a way to do something clever, perhaps very specific to GC, that would be easier than stopping all threads?

Stopping all threads is said to be easy on Windows. On Linux and Mac it may require use of a signal handler.
